Education Staff Vacancies – School director & Teachers
-
Date Posted: 2014/04/29 05:38:17
Ref. JB3045246
Job Description
The Head of School “School director" is responsible for managing the daily operation and the supervision of all staff.
The Head of School is the chief academic and administrative officer provides day-to-day direction and operational practices that represent a consistent and effective model of integrity, efficiency, and accountability. He will direct and participate in marketing and development for the school.
In addition, the Head of School performs and/or directs all other duties as, from time to time, may be assigned by the School Head Office Management.
•	Experienced Teachers in all subjects (Gulf English School) & ( A’Takamul International School)
“ Must hold Bachelor Degree, teaching diploma and a sufficient Teaching Experience”
Skills
School Director :
•	A Master’s degree in educational administration/supervision or the equivalent
•	At least three (3) years experience in educational administration
•	Demonstrated supervisory leadership
Teachers for all Subjects :
Must hold Bachelor Degree, teaching diploma and a sufficient Teaching Experience.
